org.obrel.type

Class StandardTypes

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.obrel.type.StandardTypes

  • @Annotations.RelationTypeNamespace(value="")
public class StandardTypes
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains definitions of standard relation types. It is recommended that applications use these standard types if applicable to increase the interoperability of relation-based code because using standard types allows library code and tools to access and display such relations in a standard way.

      • UPDATE_COUNTER

        public static final RelationType<java.lang.Integer> UPDATE_COUNTER
        An automatic types that counts the relation updates of a target object after it has been set on it. Depending on the target it counts the updates of the relations in a relatable object, of a relation type, or of a single relation. More specific counters can be created by using other instances of CounterType.

      • PARENT

        public static final RelationType<Relatable> PARENT
        The parent relatable object of an element in a hierarchical object structure. Applications can either use this type for their parent reference or define their own relation type with a more specific datatype and set the meta-flag MetaTypes.PARENT_ATTRIBUTE on it. Code that wants to find the parent attribute of a related object should first look for a relation type with the meta-flag set and if not found, for this type.

      • CHILDREN

        public static final RelationType<java.util.List<Relatable>> CHILDREN
        A list of the child relatable objects of an element in a hierarchical object structure. Applications can either use this type for the reference to their children or define their own relation type with a more specific datatype and set the meta-flag MetaTypes.CHILD_ATTRIBUTE on it. Code that wants to find the child attribute of a related object should first look for a relation type with the meta-flag set and if not found, for this type.
